# McRPG Skill System

## Skill vs. Ability

| Concept | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **Skill** | A leveling system (Swords, Mining, etc.). Players earn XP via actions and level up over time. |
| **Ability** | An action or passive effect unlocked/scaled by a skill. Abilities are _registered to_ a skill via `getSkillKey()`. |

Skills earn XP — abilities do the gameplay work.

## Checklist: Creating a New Skill

1. Create class in `src/main/java/us/eunoians/mcrpg/skill/impl/<name>/`
2. Extend `McRPGSkill`, implement relevant type interfaces (`ConfigurableSkill`, `HeldItemBonusSkill`, etc.)
3. Declare `static final NamespacedKey SKILL_KEY` on the class
4. Register levelable components in the constructor (`addLevelableComponent(...)`)
5. Implement `getYamlDocument()`, `getDatabaseName()`, `getPlugin()`, `getDisplayItemRoute()`
6. Create a `<Name>ConfigFile` class in `configuration/file/skill/`
7. Register in `McRPGExpansion.getSkillContent()`
8. Create abilities that return this skill's key from `getSkillKey()`

## Minimal Skill Template

```java
public final class MySkill extends McRPGSkill implements ConfigurableSkill {

    public static final NamespacedKey MY_SKILL_KEY =
        new NamespacedKey(McRPGMethods.getMcRPGNamespace(), "my_skill");

    private final McRPG mcRPG;

    public MySkill(@NotNull McRPG mcRPG) {
        super(MY_SKILL_KEY);
        this.mcRPG = mcRPG;
        // Levelable components fire when the player performs the skill action
        addLevelableComponent(new MySkillLevelOnActionComponent(), SomeEvent.class, 0);
    }

    @NotNull @Override public YamlDocument getYamlDocument() {
        return mcRPG.registryAccess().registry(RegistryKey.MANAGER).manager(McRPGManagerKey.FILE).getFile(FileType.MY_SKILL_CONFIG);
    }
    @NotNull @Override public String getDatabaseName() { return "my_skill"; }
    @NotNull @Override public Plugin getPlugin() { return mcRPG; }
    @NotNull @Override public Route getDisplayItemRoute() { return LocalizationKey.MY_SKILL_DISPLAY_ITEM; }
}
```

## Levelable Components (XP Sources)

Levelable components are registered on the skill and define which Bukkit events grant XP:

```java
// In skill constructor:
addLevelableComponent(new SwordsLevelOnAttackComponent(), EntityDamageByEntityEvent.class, 0);
```

Implement `EventLevelableComponent`:

```java
public class MySkillLevelOnActionComponent implements EventLevelableComponent {
    @Override
    public boolean shouldGrantExperience(@NotNull SkillHolder skillHolder, @NotNull Event event) {
        // return true if XP should be granted for this event
    }

    @Override
    public double getExperienceToGrant(@NotNull SkillHolder skillHolder, @NotNull Event event) {
        // return base XP amount (modifiers applied externally)
    }
}
```

## SkillHolder Data

`SkillHolder` extends `AbilityHolder` and also tracks per-skill level data:

```java
// Reading skill level data
Optional<SkillHolderData> skillData = skillHolder.getSkillHolderData(Swords.SWORDS_KEY);
skillData.ifPresent(data -> {
    int currentLevel = data.getCurrentLevel();
    double currentXp = data.getCurrentExp();
});
```

`SkillHolderData` is stored in `SkillHolder`'s data map, loaded from the database via `SkillDAO`.

## Unlock Levels

Abilities within a skill have an unlock level defined in their config. The ability becomes available to the holder only when the player's skill level reaches or exceeds the unlock threshold.

- Config location: `<skill>-config.yml`, route typically `abilities.<ability-name>.unlock-level`
- The unlock check runs when a player levels up or logs in

## HeldItemBonusSkill

Implement `HeldItemBonusSkill` if the skill gives bonuses based on the item held:

```java
@Override
public double getHeldItemBonus(@NotNull ItemStack... items) {
    ItemStack mainHand = items[0];
    CustomItemWrapper wrapper = new CustomItemWrapper(mainHand);
    // Cache route per material to avoid rebuilding it on every event
    Route route = Route.fromString(toRoutePath(MyConfigFile.MATERIAL_MODIFIERS_HEADER, materialKey));
    return getYamlDocument().getDouble(route, 1.0);
}
```

## XP Modifiers

XP modifiers are applied through the experience modifier registry before XP is granted. Do not apply modifiers inside the levelable component — the framework handles this automatically.

## Registering in McRPGExpansion

```java
// In McRPGExpansion.getSkillContent():
skillContent.addContent(new MySkill(mcRPG));
```

## Reference: Canonical Example

See `Swords.java` (`skill/impl/swords/Swords.java`) — a skill that:
- Registers a single `SwordsLevelOnAttackComponent` for `EntityDamageByEntityEvent`
- Implements `HeldItemBonusSkill` with per-material bonus caching via `CustomItemWrapper`
- Reads all config via `SwordsConfigFile` route constants
